msgctxt "RATIONALE"
msgid ""
"## Rationale\n"
"As seen in Table 1, most of the criteria for defining slums, informal "
"settlements and inadequate housing overlap. The three criteria of informal "
"settlements are essentially captured in the definition of slums, which "
"sustains the combination of both (slums/informal settlements). From the "
"seven criteria of adequate housing, the three that are not covered by slums "
"/ informal settlements are affordability, accessibility and cultural "
"adequacy. For the purpose of composing an indicator, affordability is the "
"most relevant and easier to measure.   \n"
"\n"
"Thus, in order to come up with a composite indicator, the metadata for the "
"SDG Indicator 11.1.1 is proposing to group the definition of slums and "
"informal settlements, to allow for comparison with MDGs, and add the "
"element of affordability from the definition of adequate housing. \n"
"\n"
"In this regard, *housing affordability* is not only a key housing adequacy "
"criterion, but is a suitable means of measuring inadequate housing in a "
"more encompassing manner, as it remains a global challenge across different "
"countries and income levels, with strong negative impact on urban "
"inequality. \n"
"The underlying principle is that household financial costs associated with "
"housing should not threaten or compromise the attainment and satisfaction "
"of other basic needs such as, food, education, access to health care, "
"transport, etc. Based on the existing method and data of UN-Habitat’s Urban "
"Indicators Program (1996-2006), unaffordability is currently measured as "
"the net monthly expenditure on housing cost that exceeds 30% of the total "
"monthly income of the household.\n"
"\n"
"Thus, Indicator 11.1.1 is expected to be a **composite one**, with the main "
"components of slum/informal settlements’ and the added component of "
"affordability defining inadequate housing. Table 1 details the proposed "
"definition of Slum/Informal Settlements and Inadequate Housing as well as "
"the respective measurements. \n"
"\n"
"### Table 1 – Definition and measurement criteria for slums, informal "
"settlements and inadequate housing [^12]\n"
